Cornac : PHP Code Analyzer

Usage : 
Create application.ini in ini folder, with correct MySQL access
./tokenizeur.php -d [code root] -r -g mysql,cache -I <application>.ini
./auditeur.php <application>

to extract the information : 
1) install web/index.php on your web root
  - change database access
  - change prefixe to the one used in .ini  : $prefixe = 'tu';
  - direct you browser on the index.php 
2) use the lecture_module.php file (-h for help)
3) go in the database, read the tables

Current version is DEV. 

Pre-requisite : 
PHP 5.3.1 (only tested on that version).
MySQL (should work on any version)
xdebug is used for certain debug display. 

